hpnicfPosa.name: hpnicfPosa

revisions.description: Modify the range for hpnicfPosaAppID and hpnicfPosaBackupAppID in hpnicfPosaAppTable. Modify the range for hpnicfPosaTerminalTransAppID in hpnicfPosaTerminalTable. Modify the range for hpnicfPosaMapAppID in hpnicfPosaMapTable.
The initial revision of this MIB module.

hpnicfPosa.description: This MIB is to provide the definition of the POSA (Point Of Sale Access) system.

HpnicfAppServiceType.name: HpnicfAppServiceType
HpnicfAppServiceType.description: The service type of a POS application. It means the way in which the router connects with the application server. At present, it supports two service types, tcp(1) and flow(2). If the router connects with the server through SEARIAL/ASYNC interface, the service type is flow(1). If through TCP/IP, the service type is tcp(1).

HpnicfAppMode.name: HpnicfAppMode
HpnicfAppMode.description: The work mode of a POS application. It has two value normal(1) and temporary(2). This attribute is valid only when the service type is tcp(1). If it works in temporary(2) mode, the TCP connection between router and application server is established when a POS trade begins and disconnected when a POS trade finishes. In normal(1) mode, the TCP connection is established when POS function is enabled and exists all along.

HpnicfPeerState.name: HpnicfPeerState
HpnicfPeerState.description: The current running state of the peer (application server or POS terminal) of the router. notset(1) The peer is not configured correctly. down(2) The interface connecting with the peer is down. up(3) The interface connecting with the peer is up. kept(4) The connection between router and the peer is not established. linking(5) The connection between router and the peer is establishing. linked(6) The connection between router and the peer is established. multilink(7) There are multiple connections between router and the peer. blocked(8) The connection between router and the peer is unreachable. error(9) Enable failed. The status of down(2) and up(3) appear only when the router and the peer are connected with interface. The status about TCP connections appear when the router and the peer are connected with TCP/IP.

HpnicfTerminalAccessType.name: HpnicfTerminalAccessType
HpnicfTerminalAccessType.description: The access type of a POS terminal. Now it supports 3 types. fcm(1) The POS terminal connects with router through FCM interface. flow(2) The POS terminal connects with router through SERIAL, ASYNC, AM (Analog Modem) or AUX interface. tcp(3) The POS terminal connects with router through TCP/IP protocol. The default access type is fcm(2).

HpnicfTpduChangeStrategy.name: HpnicfTpduChangeStrategy
HpnicfTpduChangeStrategy.description: The strategy to modify the address of the packet from terminals before delivering it to application server. Now it supports 2 types. ChangeTpduSrc(1) Replace the source address of the packet with POSID. ChangeTpduDest(2) Replace the destination address of the packet with POSID.

hpnicfPosaServerEnable.name: hpnicfPosaServerEnable
hpnicfPosaServerEnable.description: This attribute controls the starting or stoppage of POS access function. The defalut value is disabled(1).

hpnicfPosaFcmAnswerTimeout.name: hpnicfPosaFcmAnswerTimeout
hpnicfPosaFcmAnswerTimeout.description: The maximum answer time of a POS connection through a FCM (Fast Connection Modem) interface. The answer time is the interval from the POS terminal sending request to the Router giving its reply, in units of milliseconds.

hpnicfPosaFcmTradeTimeout.name: hpnicfPosaFcmTradeTimeout
hpnicfPosaFcmTradeTimeout.description: The maximum time of a POS trade through a FCM interface, in units of milliseconds.

hpnicfPosaFcmIdleTimeout.name: hpnicfPosaFcmIdleTimeout
hpnicfPosaFcmIdleTimeout.description: The maximum idle time of a POS connection through the FCM interface, in units of seconds.

hpnicfPosaSrvStateChangeTrapEnable.name: hpnicfPosaSrvStateChangeTrapEnable
hpnicfPosaSrvStateChangeTrapEnable.description: This attribute controls whether the hpnicfPosaServerStatusChange trap will be sent or not.

hpnicfPosaAppStateChangeTrapEnable.name: hpnicfPosaAppStateChangeTrapEnable
hpnicfPosaAppStateChangeTrapEnable.description: This attribute controls whether the hpnicfPosaAppStateChange trap will be sent or not.

hpnicfPosaTerminalHangUpTrapEnable.name: hpnicfPosaTerminalHangUpTrapEnable
hpnicfPosaTerminalHangUpTrapEnable.description: This attribute controls whether the hpnicfPosaTerminalHangUp trap will be sent or not.

hpnicfPosaFcmLnkNegoFailTrapEnable.name: hpnicfPosaFcmLnkNegoFailTrapEnable
hpnicfPosaFcmLnkNegoFailTrapEnable.description: This attribute controls whether the hpnicfPosaFcmLinkNegoFailed trap will be sent or not.

hpnicfPosaFcmPhyNegoFailTrapEnable.name: hpnicfPosaFcmPhyNegoFailTrapEnable
hpnicfPosaFcmPhyNegoFailTrapEnable.description: This attribute controls whether the hpnicfPosaFcmPhyNegoFailed trap will be sent or not.

hpnicfPosaTcpConnectionNumber.name: hpnicfPosaTcpConnectionNumber
hpnicfPosaTcpConnectionNumber.description: The current number of TCP connections.

hpnicfPosaFcmConnectionNumber.name: hpnicfPosaFcmConnectionNumber
hpnicfPosaFcmConnectionNumber.description: The current number of FCM connections.

hpnicfPosaTcpConnectionTrapEnable.name: hpnicfPosaTcpConnectionTrapEnable
hpnicfPosaTcpConnectionTrapEnable.description: This attribute specifies the threshold that must be exceeded to send the hpnicfPosaTcpConnectionExceed trap.

hpnicfPosaFcmConnectionTrapEnable.name: hpnicfPosaFcmConnectionTrapEnable
hpnicfPosaFcmConnectionTrapEnable.description: This attribute specifies the threshold that must be exceeded to send the hpnicfPosaFcmConnectionExceed trap.

hpnicfPosaTcpTradeLimit.name: hpnicfPosaTcpTradeLimit
hpnicfPosaTcpTradeLimit.description: The limit of concurrent trades in one TCP connection. The value 0 means unlimited.

hpnicfPosaTcpTradeTrapEnable.name: hpnicfPosaTcpTradeTrapEnable
hpnicfPosaTcpTradeTrapEnable.description: This attribute specifies the limit that must be exceeded to send the hpnicfPosaTcpTradeExceed trap.

hpnicfPosaTcpTradeTimeout.name: hpnicfPosaTcpTradeTimeout
hpnicfPosaTcpTradeTimeout.description: The maximum interval to wait for the reply from sending the trade packet to the application server. The value 0 means wait forever.

hpnicfPosaAppTable.name: hpnicfPosaAppTable
hpnicfPosaAppTable.description: This table shows the configuration information and running status of POS application.

hpnicfPosaAppEntry.name: hpnicfPosaAppEntry
hpnicfPosaAppEntry.description: This table shows the configuration information and running status of POS application.

hpnicfPosaAppID.name: hpnicfPosaAppID
hpnicfPosaAppID.description: The identification of a POS application.

hpnicfPosaAppServiceType.name: hpnicfPosaAppServiceType
hpnicfPosaAppServiceType.description: The service type of a POS application. It means the way in which the router connects with the application server.

hpnicfPosaAppIfIndex.name: hpnicfPosaAppIfIndex
hpnicfPosaAppIfIndex.description: This attribute is the ifindex through which the router connecting with the application server, if the service type of POS application is flow(2). It is invalid if the service type is tcp(1). At preasent, it supports 5 types of interface: FCM, SERIAL, ASYNC, AM (Analog Modem) and AUX.

hpnicfPosaAppMode.name: hpnicfPosaAppMode
hpnicfPosaAppMode.description: The work mode of a POS application.

hpnicfPosaAppHostIPType.name: hpnicfPosaAppHostIPType
hpnicfPosaAppHostIPType.description: The IP address type of the application server. And now it must be IPV4. It is invalid if the service type is flow(2).

hpnicfPosaAppHostIP.name: hpnicfPosaAppHostIP
hpnicfPosaAppHostIP.description: The IP address of the application server. And now it only supports IPV4. It is invalid if the service type is flow(2).

hpnicfPosaAppHostPort.name: hpnicfPosaAppHostPort
hpnicfPosaAppHostPort.description: The listening port of the application server. If the information of the application server is not specified, this object will return the value 0. It is invalid if the service type is flow(2).

hpnicfPosaAppRouterIPType.name: hpnicfPosaAppRouterIPType
hpnicfPosaAppRouterIPType.description: The source IP address type of the access router. Now it must be ipv4. It is invalid if the service type is flow(2).

hpnicfPosaAppRouterIP.name: hpnicfPosaAppRouterIP
hpnicfPosaAppRouterIP.description: The source IP address of access router used in connecting with application server. Now it only supports ipv4. It is invalid if the service type is flow(2).

hpnicfPosaAppKeepAliveInterval.name: hpnicfPosaAppKeepAliveInterval
hpnicfPosaAppKeepAliveInterval.description: The TCP keep alive interval of the connection between the router and the application server. In unit of seconds. The default value is 2 seconds. It is valid only when the service type is tcp(1).

hpnicfPosaAppKeepAliveCount.name: hpnicfPosaAppKeepAliveCount
hpnicfPosaAppKeepAliveCount.description: The maximum number of sending TCP keep alive packets. It is valid only when the service type is tcp(1).

hpnicfPosaAppConnectTimeout.name: hpnicfPosaAppConnectTimeout
hpnicfPosaAppConnectTimeout.description: The maximum interval that the router waits for the reply from application server after sending the request for establishing a TCP connection. It is invalid if the service type is flow(2).

hpnicfPosaAppState.name: hpnicfPosaAppState
hpnicfPosaAppState.description: The current running state of application server.

hpnicfPosaAppName.name: hpnicfPosaAppName
hpnicfPosaAppName.description: The description of a POS application.

hpnicfPosaCallerIDTransEnable.name: hpnicfPosaCallerIDTransEnable
hpnicfPosaCallerIDTransEnable.description: Enable or disable the caller-id transmission function.

hpnicfPosaTpduChangeStrategy.name: hpnicfPosaTpduChangeStrategy
hpnicfPosaTpduChangeStrategy.description: Set the strategy to modify the address of the packet from terminals before delivering it to application server.

hpnicfPosaBackupAppID.name: hpnicfPosaBackupAppID
hpnicfPosaBackupAppID.description: Specify the backup application ID, 0 indicates not using backup application. It is invalid if the service type is flow(2).

hpnicfPosaQuietTimeOut.name: hpnicfPosaQuietTimeOut
hpnicfPosaQuietTimeOut.description: Specify the wait time for re-activating application server. It is invalid if the service type is flow(2).

hpnicfPosaAppHello.name: hpnicfPosaAppHello
hpnicfPosaAppHello.description: Specify the switch of hello packet for the application server.

hpnicfPosaAppHelloInterval.name: hpnicfPosaAppHelloInterval
hpnicfPosaAppHelloInterval.description: Specify the interval time in minute(s) of hello packet.

hpnicfPosaAppRouterPort.name: hpnicfPosaAppRouterPort
hpnicfPosaAppRouterPort.description: The source port of access router used in connecting with application server. 0 indicates not to specify the source port. It is valid only if the service type is tcp(1) and mode is normal(1).

hpnicfPosaTerminalTable.name: hpnicfPosaTerminalTable
hpnicfPosaTerminalTable.description: This table shows the configuration information and running status of POS terminal.

hpnicfPosaTerminalEntry.name: hpnicfPosaTerminalEntry
hpnicfPosaTerminalEntry.description: This table shows the configuration information and running status of POS terminal.

hpnicfPosaTerminalID.name: hpnicfPosaTerminalID
hpnicfPosaTerminalID.description: The identification of a POS terminal.

hpnicfPosaTerminalAccessType.name: hpnicfPosaTerminalAccessType
hpnicfPosaTerminalAccessType.description: The access type of a POS terminal.

hpnicfPosaTerminalIfIndex.name: hpnicfPosaTerminalIfIndex
hpnicfPosaTerminalIfIndex.description: The ifindex of the interface through which connects the POS terminal and the router. It is invalid if the access type is TCP.

hpnicfPosaTerminalTransAppID.name: hpnicfPosaTerminalTransAppID
hpnicfPosaTerminalTransAppID.description: The identification of the application server to which all the packets from this POS terminal will be sent. If this object is set to 0, the destination application server to which a packet from this POS terminal will be sent is determined by its TPDU (Transport Protocol Data Unit) destination address. It is invalid if the access type is TCP.

hpnicfPosaTerminalListenPort.name: hpnicfPosaTerminalListenPort
hpnicfPosaTerminalListenPort.description: The listening port accepting the connection from POS terminals. It is valid only when the access type is TCP.

hpnicfPosaTerminalState.name: hpnicfPosaTerminalState
hpnicfPosaTerminalState.description: The current running status of a POS terminal.

hpnicfPosaTerminalName.name: hpnicfPosaTerminalName
hpnicfPosaTerminalName.description: The description of a POS terminal.

hpnicfPosaTerminalCfgIfIndex.name: hpnicfPosaTerminalCfgIfIndex
hpnicfPosaTerminalCfgIfIndex.description: The ifindex of the interface on which the terminal configuration is. If it is a physical interface, its value is equal to that of hpnicfPosaTerminalIfIndex.

hpnicfPosaMapTable.name: hpnicfPosaMapTable
hpnicfPosaMapTable.description: This table describe the application-mapping information.

hpnicfPosaMapEntry.name: hpnicfPosaMapEntry
hpnicfPosaMapEntry.description: This table describe the application-mapping information.

hpnicfPosaMapDestCode.name: hpnicfPosaMapDestCode
hpnicfPosaMapDestCode.description: The destination code of the mapping item. Generally, the destination code is a 4-character-string. If the destination address in POS packet matches the code, the packet will be deliveried to the corresponding application server. If any code can not be matched, the packet will be deliveried to the default server. A special destination code, 'default', is for default mapping item.

hpnicfPosaMapAppID.name: hpnicfPosaMapAppID
hpnicfPosaMapAppID.description: The identifier of POS application. It is the index of hpnicfPosaAppTable.

hpnicfPosaMapSrcCode.name: hpnicfPosaMapSrcCode
hpnicfPosaMapSrcCode.description: The source code of the mapping item. Generally, the source code is a 4-character-string. If the source address in POS packet matches the code, the packet will be deliveried to the corresponding application server. If any code can not be matched, the packet will be deliveried to the default server. A special source code, 'default', is for default mapping item.

hpnicfPosaFcmStatConnectFailCnts.name: hpnicfPosaFcmStatConnectFailCnts
hpnicfPosaFcmStatConnectFailCnts.description: The number of connection failures because of unsuccessful negotiations.

hpnicfPosaFcmStatTransCnts.name: hpnicfPosaFcmStatTransCnts
hpnicfPosaFcmStatTransCnts.description: The number of all transactions made through the interface.

hpnicfPosaFcmStatTransSuccessCnts.name: hpnicfPosaFcmStatTransSuccessCnts
hpnicfPosaFcmStatTransSuccessCnts.description: The number of successful transactions made through the interface.

hpnicfPosaFcmStatTransCntsClear.description: Clear the number of successful transactions and all transactions.

hpnicfPosaAppDistributeErrCnts.description: The number of packets that are discarded when no corresponding POS terminal can be found.

hpnicfPosaAppInDiscardedPkts.description: The number of inbound packets that are discarded when the incoming buffer is full.

hpnicfPosaAppOutDiscardedPkts.name: hpnicfPosaAppOutDiscardedPkts
hpnicfPosaAppOutDiscardedPkts.description: The number of outbound packets that are discarded because of link errors between the router and the application server.

hpnicfPosaTerminalStatTable.description: This table shows the statistics information of application.

hpnicfPosaTerminalStatEntry.description: This table shows the statistics information of application.

hpnicfPosaTerminalRecvPkts.description: The number of packets recieved from the POS terminal.

hpnicfPosaTerminalSendPkts.name: hpnicfPosaTerminalSendPkts

hpnicfPosaTerminalErrPkts.description: The number of inbound packets that contained errors.

hpnicfPosaTerminalInDiscardedPkts.description: The number of inbound packets that are discarded when the incoming buffer is full.

hpnicfPosaTerminalOutDiscardedPkts.description: The number of outbound packets that are discarded because of link errors between the router and the POS terminal.

hpnicfPosaBatchTerminalTable.description: The table of the configuration information relevant to a batch of POS terminals.

hpnicfPosaBatchTerminalEntry.description: The configuration information relevant to a batch of POS terminals.

hpnicfPosaTcpTermStatIPMask.description: The mask associated with the IP address or the subnet. And now it only supports ipv4.

hpnicfPosaTcpTermRecvPkts.description: The number of packets recieved from the POS terminal(s).

hpnicfPosaTcpTermSendPkts.description: The number of packets sent to the POS terminal(s).

hpnicfPosaTcpTermInDiscardedPkts.description: The number of inbound packets that are discarded when the incoming buffer is full.

hpnicfPosaCallerStatEntry.description: This table shows the statistics information of terminal according the caller-ID.

hpnicfPosaTerminalHangUp.name: hpnicfPosaTerminalHangUp
hpnicfPosaTerminalHangUp.description: This trap is generated whenever the POS connection through a FCM (Fast Connection Modem) interface is hanged up by POS terminal.

hpnicfPosaFcmLinkNegoFailed.description: This trap is generated whenever the link layer negotiation is failed between the POS terminal and router through a FCM (Fast Connection Modem) interface.

hpnicfPosaFcmPhyNegoFailed.description: This trap is generated whenever the physical layer negotiation is failed between the POS terminal and router through a FCM (Fast Connection Modem) interface.

hpnicfPosaFcmConnectionExceed.description: This trap is generated whenever the number of connections exceeds the threshold.

hpnicfPosaTcpTradeExceed.description: This trap is generated whenever the number of trades in any TCP connect exceeds the limit.

hpnicfPosaAppStateChangeObject.description: This is a dummy MIB object referenced by the hpnicfPosaAppStateChange trap. This object shows the availability changing of corresponding application server.
